- API is a clean & well-defined interface that hides unnecessary detail of the
  software.
- Tools to manage API:
  - Cloud Endpoints:
    - distributed API management system
    - provides an API console, hosting, logging, monitoring, and other features
      to help you create, share, maintain, and secure your APIs.
    - API must support the OpenAPI Specification.
    - supports applications running in App Engine, Google Kubernetes Engine,
      and Compute Engine.
    - Clients include Android, iOS, and Javascript.
  - Apigee Edge:
    - focus on business problems, like rate limiting, quotas, and analytics.
    - Backend services for Apigee Edge don't have to be in Google Cloud.
    - Often used to provide a software service to other companies.
